author: Mike Wall
title: Mars Rover Curiosity Snaps Beautiful Selfie After Rare Chemistry Experiment - Space.com
description: Curiosity did some "wet chemistry" for just the second time ever.
content:
NASA's Curiosity rover took this selfie on Oct. 11, 2019, the 2,553rd Martian day, or sol, of its mission. The rover drilled twice in this location, which is nicknamed "Glen Etive."
